'''American Business Media''' is an association of business information providers that was founded in 1906. Currently, the association has more than 300 member companies and delivers [[business intelligence]] to [[industry]], [[advertising|Madison Avenue]], [[finance|Wall Street]] and the [[politics|Beltway]], representing almost 5,000 print and online titles as well as 1,000 trade shows. <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.americanbusinessmedia.com/abm/About.asp?SnID=572707158 |title=American Business Media - About Us |access-date=2007-07-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928023611/http://www.americanbusinessmedia.com/abm/About.asp?SnID=572707158 |archive-date=2007-09-28 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

ABM also sponsors the annual Jesse H. Neal Awards, rewarding editorial excellence in business-to-business publications.<ref>[http://www.americanbusinessmedia.com/abm/Neal.asp American Business Media - Neal Awards] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071006231042/http://www.americanbusinessmedia.com/abm/Neal.asp |date=2007-10-06 }}</ref>

