'''Chung Yong-jin''' (born 19 September 1968) is a [[South Korea]]n businessman, the [[vice chairman]] and [[CEO]] of [[Shinsegae|Shinsegae Group]]. He is the son of [[Lee Myung-hee]], chairman of [[Shinsegae|Shinsegae Group]].

==Education==
Chung graduated from [[Kyungbock High School]]. He has a [[Bachelor of Arts]] in [[Economics]] from  [[Brown University]].

