'''Geir Elsebutangen''' (born 3 January 1964) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] politician for the [[Conservative Party (Norway)|Conservative Party]].
He has served as an elected member of [[Skien]] [[municipal council (Norway)|city council]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ta.no/motor/article6931129.ece|title=Lager alternativ til bypakka|last=Johannessen|first=Bjørn|date=19 October 2013|work=Telemarksavisa|language=Norwegian|accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref> In the [[Norwegian parliamentary election, 2013|2013 election]] he was elected as a deputy representative to the [[Parliament of Norway]] from [[Telemark]].<ref>{{stortingetbio|GEIE}}</ref>
Since 2013 he works as the chief executive officer of Kragerø Energi.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kv.no/nyheter/elsebutangen-ny-direktor-i-kragero-energi-1.7877680|title=Elsebutangen ny direktør i Kragerø Energi|last=Selås|first=Elin Frisch|author2=Hartviksen, Tom Martin Kj.|date=9 May 2013|work=Kragerø Blad Vestmar|language=Norwegian|accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref>
