{{Infobox officeholder |name = Lawrence Kelly |image = |office = Mayor of Cudahy, Wisconsin |term_start = 1964 |term_end = 1988 |predecessor = |successor = Raymond Glowacki |state1 = [[Wisconsin]] |district1 = |term_start1 = |term_end1 = |predecessor1 = |successor1 = |state_senate2 = |district2 = |term_start2 = |term_end2 = |predecessor2 = |successor2 = |state_assembly3 = Wisconsin |district3 = 24th |term_start3 = 1963 |term_end3 = 1964 |predecessor3 = |successor3 = |birth_date = {{birth date|1913|12|18}} |birth_place = [[Sparta, Wisconsin]] |death_date = {{death date and age|1999|8|23|1913|12|18}} |death_place = [[Cudahy, Wisconsin]] |spouse = Bernice (July 21, 1914-September 13, 2005) (aged 91) |children = James |alma_mater = |religion = |website = }}
'''Lawrence P. Kelly''' (December 18, 1913 &ndash; August 23, 1999) was an [[United States|American]] [[accountant]] and [[business manager]] from [[Cudahy, Wisconsin|Cudahy]], [[Wisconsin]] who served one term (1963-1964) as a [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] member of the [[Wisconsin State Assembly]] from [[Milwaukee County, Wisconsin|Milwaukee County]]'s 24th district.<ref>'Wisconsin Blue Book 1964,' Biographical Sketch of Lawrence P. Kelly, pg. 58</ref>
Born in [[Sparta, Wisconsin]], Kelly moved to Cudahy with his family. He managed movie theaters. He also served as mayor of Cudahy 1964-1988.<ref>[https://docs.legis.wisconsin.gov/1999/related/enrolled/ajr73 Assembly Joint Assembly 73]</ref>
